WYSI*not*WYG project
(What You See Is *NOT* What You Get)

Anarchitecture Ile-de-France

This animated photograph is from the series Anarchitecture Ile-de-France made with digital photography. 

The original photographic series was presented at Parcourir les Puzzles exhibition  from April to May, 2012 / Evry, France
Curated by Nicolas Rosette

Specs:
1080*1920, 25 fps

Anarchitecture is an ongoing photographic series from the WYSI*not*WYG project.
Using fragmented images of a city photograph from around the world, the process remakes our urban landscape through digitally processed photos that break down and offer a new version of the reality of our day-to-day urban environment.
